    <title>Tropical convex hulls of infinite sets</title>
    <summary>  In this paper we study the interplay between tropical convexity and its
classical counterpart. In particular, we focus on the tropical convex hull of
convex sets and polyhedral complexes. %First we investigate the structure of
the tropical convex hull of any set and then convex sets in particular. We give
a vertex description of the tropical convex hull of a line segment and of a ray
in $\mathbb{R}^n/\mathbb {R}\mathbf{1}$ and show that tropical convex hull and
classical convex hull commute in $\mathbb{R}^3/\mathbb {R}\mathbf{1}$. Finally
we prove results on the dimension of tropically convex fans and give a lower
bound on the degree of a tropical curve under certain hypotheses.
</summary>
